            <div class="pdp-faq-a">
              <p><strong>Yes — but different from caffeine.</strong> Cordyceps doesn't stimulate your adrenals like coffee does; it supports your body's natural ATP production at the cellular level. The result is steady, even energy — no peak, no crash, no jitters. Most customers describe it as "a calm second wind."</p>
            </div>
          </details>

