            </summary>
            <div class="pdp-faq-a">
              <p><strong>Yes — designed for exactly this.</strong> Happie is what many of our customers reach for during their first few weeks off coffee. The Cordyceps provides the steady energy your body misses, the Lion's Mane handles the focus piece (the part most people fear losing when they quit caffeine), and the Reishi softens the cortisol rebound. <em>The transition with Happie feels nothing like quitting cold.</em></p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="pdp-faq-item">
            <summary class="pdp-faq-q">
              <span class="pdp-faq-icon"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 3h6l1 4H8L9 3z"/><path d="M8 7v10a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h6a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V7"/><path d="M12 11v3M11 13h2"/></svg></span>
              <span>Is it actually safe? Has it been lab tested?</span>
              <span class="pdp-faq-chev"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pdp-faq-a">
              <p><strong>Every single batch is third-party tested at KCA Laboratories</strong> (ISO/IEC 17025:2017 accredited, Nicholasville KY). We test for heavy metals, 66 pesticides, microbials, mycotoxins, and residual solvents. <a href="/pages/the-science#lab-results">Download the COA for your batch →</a></p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="pdp-faq-item">
            <summary class="pdp-faq-q">
              <span class="pdp-faq-icon"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 11.5a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9 3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1-7.6 4.7 8.38 8.38 0 0 1-3.8-.9L3 21l1.9-5.7a8.38 8.38 0 0 1-.9-3.8 8.5 8.5 0 0 1 4.7-7.6 8.38 8.38 0 0 1 3.8-.9h.5a8.48 8.48 0 0 1 8 8v.5z"/></svg></span>
              <span>Will it help with focus / ADHD / brain fog?</span>
              <span class="pdp-faq-chev"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pdp-faq-a">
              <p><strong>900mg Lion's Mane is the dose used in cognitive-focus studies</strong> (most show benefit at 500–3,000mg daily). It supports nerve growth factor (NGF) — the protein involved in neuron maintenance and signal clarity. We can't make medical claims for ADHD or brain fog (we're not a drug), but many of our daily customers report a noticeably clearer headspace within 2–4 weeks. If you're on ADHD medication, talk to your doctor before adding any new supplement.</p>
